Name: Powerful Earthquake
Description: A powerful earthquake destroys large portions of the Walls of Constantinople, including 57 towers.

Name: Synod of Rome
Description: Synod of Rome: Emperor Otto I calls a council at St. Peter's Basilica in Rome. Pope John XII is deposed on charges of an armed rebellion against Otto.

Name: Charter of the Forest
Description: 1217 – The Charter of the Forest is sealed at St Paul's Cathedral, London by King Henry III, acting under the regency of William Marshall, 1st Earl of Pembroke which re-establishes for free men rights of access to the royal forest that had been eroded by William the Conqueror and his heirs.

Name: Great Comet of 1577
Description: 1577 – The first recorded observation from Earth of the Great Comet of 1577 takes place by Aztec astronomers in Mexico, followed by reports from Italy on November 7 and Japan on November 8. Astronomer Tycho Brahe will track the comet from November 13 until January 26 before it departs the Solar System.

Name: Battle of Jemappes
Description: 1792 – Battle of Jemappes in the French Revolutionary Wars.

Name: Abraham Lincoln
Description: 1860 – Abraham Lincoln is elected the 16th president of the United States with only 40% of the popular vote, defeating John C. Breckinridge, John Bell, and Stephen A. Douglas in a four-way race.

Name: New Brunswick, New Jersey
Description: 1869 – In New Brunswick, New Jersey, Rutgers College defeats Princeton University (then known as the College of New Jersey), 6–4, in the first official intercollegiate American football game.

Name: William McKinley
Description: 1900 – President William McKinley is re-elected, along with his vice-presidential running mate, Governor Theodore Roosevelt of New York. Republicans also swept the congressional elections, winning increased majorities in both the Senate and the House of Representatives.

Name: Spanish Civil War
Description: 1936 – Spanish Civil War: The republican government flees from Madrid to Valencia, leading to the formation of the Madrid Defense Council in its stead.

Name: World War II
Description: 1943 – World War II: The 1st Ukrainian Front liberates Kyiv from German occupation.

Name: Meet the Press
Description: 1947 – Meet the Press, the longest running television program in history, makes its debut on NBC Television.

Name: Nguyễn Ngọc Thơ
Description: 1963 – Nguyễn Ngọc Thơ is appointed to head the South Vietnamese government by General Dương Văn Minh's junta, five days after the latter deposed and assassinated President Ngô Đình Diệm.

Name: United States Atomic Energy Commission
Description: 1971 – The United States Atomic Energy Commission tests the largest U.S. underground hydrogen bomb, code-named Cannikin, on Amchitka Island in the Aleutians.

Name: Uttawar forced sterilisations
Description: 1976  -  Uttawar forced sterilisations: Mass vasectomy of nearly 800 men of Uttawar village, Palwal district, Haryana during India's Emergency imposed by Indira Gandhi.

Name: Kelly Barnes Dam
Description: 1977 – The Kelly Barnes Dam, located above Toccoa Falls College near Toccoa, Georgia, fails, killing 39.

Name: Colombian conflict
Description: 1985 – Colombian conflict, leftist guerrillas of the 19th of April Movement seize control of the Palace of Justice in Bogotá.

Name: Sumburgh disaster
Description: 1986 – Sumburgh disaster: A British International Helicopters Boeing 234LR Chinook crashes 2.mw-parser-output .frac{white-space:nowrap}.mw-parser-output .frac .num,.mw-parser-output .frac .den{font-size:80%;line-height:0;vertical-align:super}.mw-parser-output .frac .den{vertical-align:sub}.mw-parser-output .sr-only{border:0;clip:rect(0,0,0,0);clip-path:polygon(0px 0px,0px 0px,0px 0px);height:1px;margin:-1px;overflow:hidden;padding:0;position:absolute;width:1px}1⁄2 miles east of Sumburgh Airport killing 45 people. It is the deadliest civilian helicopter crash on record.

Name: Lancang–Gengma earthquakes
Description: 1988 – Lancang–Gengma earthquakes: At least 730 are killed after two powerful earthquakes rock the China–Myanmar border in Yunnan Province.

Name: Cleveland Browns relocation controversy
Description: 1995 – Cleveland Browns relocation controversy: Art Modell announces that he signed a deal that would relocate the Cleveland Browns to Baltimore.

Name: Jiang Lijun
Description: 2002 – Jiang Lijun is detained by Chinese police for signing the Open Letter to the 16th National Congress of the Chinese Communist Party.

Name: Fokker 50
Description: 2002   – A Fokker 50 crashes near Luxembourg Airport, killing 20 and injuring three.

Name: express train collides
Description: 2004 – An express train collides with a stationary car near the village of Ufton Nervet, England, killing seven and injuring 150.

Name: Tammy Baldwin
Description: 2012 – Tammy Baldwin becomes the first openly gay politician to be elected to the United States Senate.

Name: Syrian civil war
Description: 2016 – Syrian civil war: The Syrian Democratic Forces (SDF) launch an offensive to capture the city of Raqqa from the Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant (ISIL).
